troduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Tilley was born about 1395, in Bedfordshire, England. He had at least 1 son with Mrs William Tilley. He died after 1412."},"et":{"about 1395–after 1412":"umbes 1395–pärast 1412","1385–Female":"1385–Surnud","1413–1469":"1413–1469","1395–1412":"1395–1412","after 1412":"pärast 1412","1469":"1469","1413":"1413","1412":"1412","1385":"1385","1395":"1395","about 1395":"umbes 1395","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England",", , , England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1395–after 1412":"noin 1395–1412 jälkeen","1385–Female":"1385–Kuollut","1413–1469":"1413–1469","1395–1412":"1395–1412","after 1412":"1412 jälkeen","1469":"1469","1413":"1413","1412":"1412","1385":"1385","1395":"1395","about 1395":"noin 1395","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England",", , , England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1395–after 1412":"environ 1395–après 1412","1385–Female":"1385–Décédée","1413–1469":"1413–1469","1395–1412":"1395–1412","after 1412":"après 1412","1469":"1469","1413":"1413","1412":"1412","1385":"1385","1395":"1395","about 1395":"environ 1395","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Angleterre",", , , England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William Tilley est né environ 1395, à Bedfordshire, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs William Tilley. Il est décédé après 1412."},"de":{"about 1395–after 1412":"um 1395–nach 1412","1385–Female":"1385–Verstorben","1413–1469":"1413–1469","1395–1412":"1395–1412","after 1412":"nach 1412","14